A lot of older films have relatively simple plots, but you can see they are intended for a very neurologically intelligent audience, e.g. a lot of characters are introduced quickly one after the other and the viewer is meant to remember all their names after a single mention.

Newer movies are made for subclinical autists who will repeatedly forget characters' names, struggle to remember faces, have trouble following the plot, etc. Even if the story is more convoluted and complicated it always assumes the viewer is more stupid on the biological level.

One thing most people would be surprised about is that it's actually relatively easy to consciously change your natural gait by just intentionally imitating someone else's gait from videos of him walking for some time. You can even "pirate" the artificial gait of film characters.

I guess it's similar to how Dr. Buteyko guys change their natural breathing pattern to retain more CO2 in day to day life without doing it consciously 24/7 outside of some exercises... But just observing someone's gait and imitating it is enough to set it as your default in days.

This really is the fundamental pattern of modern decay: analog technology replaced with digital technology, physical objects with online data, always tending towards the psychic realm of numbers and away from the material world's grounding, towards mirages of pure quantity.

Even the Broda Barnes-Uriah neurological degeneration phenomenon observation trends towards the pattern: People who are more opinionated and less good at reading and less well-read, larger athletes gymcelling away with poorer grip strength, oversocialized people with dull voices.
